page.title: 12WARNACT around Bubbenhall
page.content: WARNACT-Warwickshire Nature Conservation Trust-is one of the 44 different county trusts,all part of the Royal Society for Nature Conservation.Formed in 1970,the Trust owns or leases many acres of nature reserves throughout Warwickshire, including Ryton Woods,Ryton Pool and Ryton Gravel Pits.The Trust is entirely voluntary,its only regular income being from members dues.WARNACT gives farmers advice on conservation, liaises with a variety of local Councils and other official bodies, visits schools and clubs to give more people the chance to be involved in actual conservation projects.In choosing sites,priority is given to outstanding beauty,scientific interest or survival.A growing emphasis is now being placed on developing habitats that are urban or man-made.
